<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-08-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-08-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName>
                                to Prime Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                            </hi><note n="1" xml:id="d202fn1">Delivered to the British Joint Staff
                                Mission at Washington for transmission to <gloss target="#t_Churchill1">Churchill</gloss> at Quebec.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-08-11">11 August 1943</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>344. Your number 407.<note n="2" xml:id="d202fn2">
                                <hi rend="italic">Supra.</hi>
                            </note>
                        </p>
                        <p>Regret delay in replying. Suggest thin clothes but be prepared for a
                            variety of weather. Delighted to see you in any costume.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>